ported_tracking_modes": [], "user_interaction_modes": ["MULTI_USER"], "id": "8053210501471927"}, "review_messages": ["", "", "1. Thank you for your submission. Your app includes one or more cover art assets with text outside of the restricted frame (top or bottom 20% of the image or 10% on the sides). The top and the bottom 20% and 10% on sides of your cover art must be free of text. Please remove this text and resubmit.\n2.Thank you for your submission. Your app includes one or more cover art assets with text outside of the restricted frame (top or bottom 20% of the image or 10% on the sides). The top and the bottom 20% and 10% on sides of your cover art must be free of text. Please remove this text and resubmit.\n3. \"The right to deletion must be applicable to all users regardless of region. Please clarify in your Privacy Policy that the right to deletion is for all users.  For more information: https://developer.oculus.com/policy/data-use/ & https://developer.oculus.com/blog/working-together-to-protect-peoples-privacy/.\n\nNeed help with the Privacy Policy? Get the clarity you need fast with our new Privacy Policy video course featuring tips and resources from Meta experts: https://app.dataprotocol.com/container/60?utm_source=MQ&utm_medium=email&utm_id=pp&utm_content=app_review.\"\n4. The user is unable to interact with all in-app elements while sitting. To qualify for the \"Sitting\" Supported Player Mode, the app must provide a way for the user to interact with all critical functionality elements.  Alternatively, you may change your application's metadata to reflect the Standing/Roomscale nature of the application.  More information can be found at https://developer.oculus.com/learn/design-accessible-vr-locomotion/\n5. When caught by the monster, the user is caught in a loop unable to move and they become stuck. There is no way to reset the player\u2019s position or the scene without exiting the application.\n6. The app runs noticeably lower than 60 frames per second on supported devices. Please refer to https://developer.oculus.com/blog/how-to-optimize-your-oculus-quest-app-w-renderdoc-walkthroughs-of-key-usage-scenarios-and-optimization-tips-part-1/ and https://developer.oculus.com/blog/how-to-optimize-your-oculus-quest-app-w-renderdoc-walkthroughs-of-key-usage-scenarios-and-optimization-tips-part-2/?locale=en_US"]}]}, "cover_square_image": {"uri": "https://scontent-lga3-1.oculuscdn.com/v/t64.5771-25/39031359_387467107580821_2830420834373503656_n.png?stp=dst-png_s360x360&_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=6e7a0a&_nc_ohc=kwtksepU968Q7kNvgGMj4Bb&_nc_zt=3&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-1.oculuscdn.com&oh=00_AYB5D2cMgVoAhLO00Cf8kTtrj2r1qmDG0HNx6PGHThJhAQ&oe=675FFC1C"}, "is_concept": false, "is_test": false, "is_trial_offer_valid": false, "display_name": "Bloodless", "platform": "ANDROID_6DOF", "context_category": {"context_category": "GAMES", "id": "2743326035925534"}, "context_topics": [{"topic_name": "Action", "id": "459781504968480"}], "release_date": 1727824080, "lastRevision": {"nodes": [{"id": "7768109119982068", "release_type": "SCHEDULED", "administration_status": "APPROVED", "pdp_metadata": {"application": {"default_locale": "en_US", "id": "7768109089982071", "is_first_party": false, "enables_in_app_ads": false, "is_concept": false, "platform": "ANDROID_6DOF"}, "iarc_cert": {"id": "1017426146783201"}, "iarc_email": null, "msrp": null, "translations": {"nodes": [{"images": {"nodes": [{"file_name": "image (1).png", "id": "2859995087474016", "image_type": "APP_IMG_COVER_LANDSCAPE", "uri": "https://scontent-lga3-2.oculuscdn.com/v/t64.5771-25/75429290_2859995090807349_2672987239205654210_n.png?_nc_cat=100&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=6e7a0a&_nc_ohc=NVy0dDC9fZYQ7kNvgHL9em2&_nc_zt=3&_nc_ht=scontent-lga3-2.oculuscdn.com&oh=00_AYBAFOu5nioPEnrfhbB4v4uASqfFwqRoMgFCcHh3lm2syg&oe=676020AF"}, {"file_name": "MainScene_Custom..._19.09.2024_15-57-20.png", "id": "1803604120170967", "image_type": "APP_IMG_COVER_PORTRAIT", "uri": "https://scontent-lga3-2.oculuscd